    <!-- SECTION: TRACKING -->
    <h2>Why This Changes How You Track</h2>

    <p>If you're currently counting collagen grams toward your daily protein target, you're likely overstating your effective muscle-building protein by 10–20g per day. For a man targeting 130g, that's the difference between hitting the target and falling 15% short — in the range where muscle preservation starts to slip.</p>

    <p>The fix is simple: track your complete protein separately from your collagen supplement. Count whey, casein, eggs, meat, dairy, fish, and legumes toward your muscle protein goal. Let collagen be a separate supplement that doesn't inflate your number.</p>

    <p>This is one of the cases where <a href="https://snapprotein.com/blog/best-protein-tracking-app/">a simple protein tracker</a> pays for itself — not because tracking is complicated, but because it makes the distinction visible. When you can see your number clearly, you can see when collagen is padding it artificially.</p>

